    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small, indoor caps with a single or double frill as a border to the front only, ending at the ears; worn by women in the 18th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
